 1. File Compression

 `gzip` – Compress a file
Reduces file size, adds `.gz` extension.

```bash
gzip [options] filename
 gunzip [options] filename.gz
 grep "word" filename
awk '{print $1}' filename   # prints first column
sed 's/old/new/' filename
echo "hello" > day.txt
echo "welcome to day 3" >> day3.txt   # appends to file
